he second is to modify the localization assumptions used to solve edge problems. Our numerical tests show that both strategies lead to a significant reduction of the iterations and suggest that efficient MMsFV methods can be obtained by identifying optimal smoothers or devising better localizations for the edge problems. {\textcopyright} 2013 Elsevier Inc.},
